claim: The river forming a boundary between Earth and the Underworld in Greek mythology is the source of the name for the moon Styx.
premise_source_doc_sentence: In Greek mythology , Styx  (  -LSB- stɪks -RSB- Στύξ -LSB- stýkʰs -RSB-  )  is a deity and a river that forms the boundary between Earth and the Underworld  (  the domain often called Hades , which also is the name of its ruler  )  .
